annotation.TEXT: Note: There was one late vote for GSP, so that level actually got 11 votes, which doesn't change anything.

Yeah, that was a literal wall of text there, which combined all of the votes from the last four episodes! I had to rearrange the silly votes quite a bit to make them fit without resorting to shrinking the font, but I made it work! Alright, so Green Switch Palace is my next stop!
Aw, come on. No space launch there?
That's two...
What hit me?! ...Aw, I think there are so many sprites present that one of the regular Boos in this room became invisible, and that's what I hit.
Alright, there's the keyhole, and a Fudge Stripe Cookie that I've just gotta have...
Hmm... Looks like that brown platform is just gonna continue rising slowly without doing anything else. Oh, and speaking of brown platforms...
I'm pretty sure the key is in that ? block, but I'll worry about dealing with that puzzle on my second visit.

Now, actually, waffledoctor87 had told me that the farthest he had tweaked in this hack was Donut Secret (1) and Donut (Ghost) House, except for a little thing in Forest of Illusion 4 (which I think was just the Lakitu throwing fish, which we already saw in NO Block Randomness earlier). So, I guess I'm done now...
Nope, doesn't look like it. However, I'm going to play through it anyway, for one very good reason, which you've likely guessed by now...
Hmm... Somehow, I don't think this area has been edited. But, there are red koopas, so you know what that means!

Maybe I got them all? Who knows. Well, there's a barely visible light green wall triangle here. I wonder why the floating coins were made invisible instead of just having their color changed to green as well...
Oops, I think I forgot to speed up this little return trip to the keyhole, but that's okay. It won't take very long.
Bonus game average so far: 30 / 4 = 7.5 1-ups each.
Also, green parakoopas, which are certainly fitting in this place.
And there it is!
Almost didn't make it to this balloon.
Super Yoshi Stomp Finisher! Blaster Combo! (9 hits) 2-life combo!
And, you know what? I want to go back into that side area again for the Fudge Stripe Cookie I missed.
50-star hits: 3 Goal tape average so far: 434 / 9 = 48.222 stars each.
NOOOOO, YOSHIII!!! Stupid bullet taking advantage of my current hastiness!
Huh, seems like there are invisible coins around here.
Maybe I should concentrate on getting the Fudge Stripe Cookies and 1-up at the top of this room right now.
UPDATE: I accidentally overlooked a vote for Super Mario 63. Sorry about that!

Okay, now Donut Secret came in second, so that's where I'm going next! (BTW, votes for Donut Secret 1 back in episode 6 counted towards Donut Secret here, since it's the same level, just with the "1" removed from its name.)
D'oh!
A sada, suludo brzine bonus igru!
Yep, as I thought, that coin arrow pointed to a hidden block, which I can then stand on to activate the eating block below.
Hi, Yoshi! I'll try not to let you get shot from behind this time!
Well, I saw the very tip of a gray platform to my left launch into space, so that counts. However, that's not the only thing that happened! Whoa!
...Or that either! LOL!
Oh, that would be a neat way to do a shell jump. Can I try that again?
Ah, but the "paranormal activity" that can affect some sprites will now linger around for as long as I remain in this area!
Why am I wasting time getting this flower that I don't really need? I have no idea.
There's my sixth Fudge Stripe Cookie in this level...
Maybe the poltergeists can help me reach the other Fudge Stripe Cookie? ...Nope, doesn't look like it. Nuts!
D'oh!
No Yoshis because they'd lose their lunch at this speed.

...Except I'm not! I actually peeked a little bit ahead off camera, and found one more tweak, in Donut Secret House! Now, most of the level is unchanged, so I'll just ludicrously speed through all that...
Alright, enough silliness. Let's enter this bonus room, and I think I'll actually try playing it out without abusing the cape spin trick.
Well, that only sorta worked, and I would've had to leave Yoshi behind if I wanted to bounce to the pipe on that attempt. Let's just fly up to the pipe instead.
Too bad there weren't more red koopas in this level, and I don't feel like backtracking to eat the one that this level does have again.
Go, my Christmas-green ! blocks, and fill the world with your jolly greenness!
Huh, I think I threw that ice block at the exact frame it would've melted there, which extended its life span by... about half a second. Yay. Alright, now let's do this puzzle the proper way.

Well, that didn't accomplish much... Huh? Wait, the koopa is still in the shell, even though it went into Yoshi's mouth! Is that because the shell came from a block? Or is that the result of one of waffledoctor87's tweaks?
Oh, and of course, I'm intentionally not going to abuse the left+right glitch here.
Okay, can we please have a space launch this time?
I wonder where all of the invisible coins are? I'll fly around a little bit...
Okay, hopefully the big guy still only takes 3 hits, so I should be able to win with minimal movement now. Just make sure I keep facing to the right as much as I can.

Ho ho ho! I wonder if you guys were expecting me to upload another Super Tweak World episode today... Well, I obviously did! So, let's take a look at those voting results to see where I'll be heading next...
BGM: DKC3 - Jangle Bells
WHEEEE!!! (That would've sucked if I missed the keyhole after flinging the cloud like that... Well, maybe not, since I probably could've flown to the keyhole if that happened.)
Space launch count: 19
Heh, caught the wall with my dive bomb there.
Ah, this cool black cannon is safe to touch. (Also, off camera, I did a "science" later on, touching a red cannon, and it's not insta-kill, instead acting like munchers.)

Yes! ...Whoa! I'm glad I had jumped off of that yellow block on the left, or I would've been Kaizo trapped! I guess it was another turn block bridge, and only the center block was visible due to the same sprite memory issue that made that one Boo invisible.
Oh, nice. There's another cloud right there for me when I came out of the pipe there.

Aw, I was hoping to launch the balloon into space, but thinking about it now, I think the space launch only occurs on sprites in certain sprite slots, and typically won't affect items that come out of blocks.
Yep, this Big Boo Boss room has been tweaked! It's now trickier, and features Deadly Acid of Death™, and... What the?!
Well, that sucked. Alright, let's get the last Fudge Stripe Cookie and finish the level.
Looks like the bullets that the red hot cannons fire are totally safe to stomp.
Very good, unlike that last time where I screwed up the first panel!
Whoa, what the? This platform teleported into the middle of its loop, and it's just sitting there, rising slowly.
Whoa, I wasn't expecting that to happen...
Aha! A red koopa! Now, let's go to a place where I can see multiple moving platforms and see if I can launch some of them...
Yeah, that attempt to shell jump was never gonna work.
Time for some ludicrous speed!
switchpalacecorner still resides here, and nothing's changed in this room besides the color palette.
Oh, what? That invisible Boo made it all the way over there already? Okay, this is getting serious. One more hit and I'm done!
Oh, geez! What the heck is with this one rotating gray platform?! Wow, this is silly!
Alright, it's boss time! (And it may as well be final boss time for now!)
Alright, now for the secret exit, and I'm going to speed up most of the footage on this second visit...
Well, that might've worked if I had been ready to catch the key there. Alright, I'm going to ludicrous speed for a moment while I use the side area to reset the puzzle...
Uh, oh. I wasted too much time. I don't think I'll be able to get everything up there...
Thank you!
If I stand around until the platform reaches the top of the looping guide-line, will it do anything special? Let's find out... (Also, there's a gray platform over here that's ascending into heaven.)
9-life combo!
Goal tape average: 474 / 10 = 47.4 stars each.

That leads to the Donut Secret House, which I'll get to eventually. However, Donut Plains 3 came in third in the voting, so I'm going to play that one next... After I get a Yoshi from the Top Banana Zone first, that is!
Sacrificial horse count: 2
Oh, neat! I did the double item glitch there! ...But, I don't know if I actually wanted to do that, since that got rid of my reserve flower... Well, I'm sure I'll find more flowers in this level.
Heh, I'm now riding in two clouds at once, I think.
Can I get 50 one more time? That would be so sweet...
Nope. Oh, well. That's still a really nice average, and getting 50 once today was still sweet.
The poltergeists are back at it again, and some of the moving platforms around here are doing really weird things now!
Oh, looks like that brown platform is acting normally now. But, the same can't be said for these checkered platforms!
Alright, Yoshi. Let's get a move on here.
Oh, man. Red hot bullet blasters. I'll try not to touch them.
And that's how I'm sure the puzzle was intended to go. Alright, let's quickly bring this key over to the keyhole...
D'oh!
Whoa, careful! I definitely don't want to lose Yoshi in a dumb way, at least not yet!
Well, that line-guided platform just said "Screw this! I'm outta here!", but what if I turn the switch OFF and then make it respawn?
Space launch count: 18
Got it, but I'm now low on time!
Whoa, jackpot! I think my goal tape average should be able to remain over 45 for quite some time!
Alright, there's the block that I suspect holds the key. Now, I'm pretty sure I know what I'm meant to do here, but let's see if I can get to the ? block in a different way...
Alright, there's the seventh and last Fudge Stripe Cookie of this level, and I think I'll have just enough time to reach the goal...
Oh, it looks like it's behaving normally now. It must be in a different, unaffected sprite slot now. However, this kooper is under the poltergeists' power, and so are 2 Fuzzies!

And, I believe that's it for all of the tweaks in this version of the hack (except for FoI4, which I'm not bothering with). Now, waffledoctor87 did send me yet another updated version, but I want to take a break from Super Tweak World for a while. So, until next time folks, when I'll be doing something else!
Merry Christmas to all, and to all a good night... Yo!
So, I've got this Lakitu cloud here, which is nice, because I'd probably have a hard time navigating through this level otherwise (unless I did a lot of tricky cape flying).
Alright, that time, the koopa vanished from the shell after it went into Yoshi's mouth.
Uh, oh. There's some Deadly Acid of Death™. I'd better be careful. Also, this ? block has a green shell, which I guess is fitting.
Now, has DP3 been tweaked at all?
Descend faster, Mario!
Now, I'm seriously tempted to use the left+right glitch here, but I want to see if I can make it in time without the glitch.
...Oh? There's no water? Definitely an interesting tweak, changing this level into a non-watery cave level. No wonder the level dot on the map was for an underground level!
